* {{cite web|last1=Jan|first1=Retsö|title=Arabs (historical)|url=http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/encyclopaedia-of-islam-3/arabs-historical-COM_22957?s.num=41&s.rows=50&s.start=40|language=en}}
* {{cite web|title=The origin of the word "Arab"|url=http://www.ismaili.net/histoire/history03/history302.html|website=Ismaili.net|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> [[Tribes of Arabia|Arab tribes]], most notably the [[Ghassanids]] and [[Lakhmids]], begin to appear in the southern [[Syrian Desert]] from the mid 3rd century CE onward, during the mid to later stages of the [[Roman Empire|Roman]] and [[Sasanian Empire|Sasanian]] empires.<ref>
